Sentencas: Solid-oxide fuel cell components were fabricated using an atmospheric plasma spraying method.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM), 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (8YSZ), ceria (CeO2), and YSZ-NiO powders were used as feedstock materials for layered deposition of cathode, electrolyte, and anode, respectively, to make a complete cell.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: In this work, two types of electrolyte materials were investigated, viz., 8YSZ and the one containing 10 wt.% CeO2.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Because a high densification is expected in the solid oxide electrolyte (as opposed to observed porosity of similar to 27%), current work focuses only on the nanomechanical evaluation of the same.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) images show the retention of nanocrystallinity in the plasma-sprayed deposits.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Elemental analyses via energy-dispersive spectroscopy revealed chemically distinct identities of the cell components ruling out diffusion or reaction at the boundaries.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Porosity values vary between 29.0% and 35.4% in anode and 42.9-48.4% in cathode, indicating appreciable achievement for high performance of electrode materials.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: The addition of 10 wt.% ceria to 8YSZ has shown enhancement in the elastic modulus and hardness of the electrolyte material by 18.4 GPa and 1.6 GPa, respectively.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte

Sentencas: Theoretical estimation of thermal conductivity of the plasma-sprayed materials has been found to be in the order of 2.27-4.45 W/mK.
Titulo: Nanomechanical Properties and Thermal Conductivity Estimation of Plasma-Sprayed, Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell Components: Ceria-Doped, Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte
